@DATABASE "Default"
@Ver$ "FontLook V2.80 (08/12/97)"
@author "Heiko Schr—der"
@Index MAIN
@remark requires MultiView

@NODE "Main" "FontLook 2.80 for Finalwriter"
@TOC "MAIN"

                               @{fg shine}£FontLook 2.80¨@{fg text}

is an ARexx-Script for Finalwriter to get an overview about @{fg fill}individual@{fg text} fonts.


                           @{" " link "Install"} Installation

                           @{" " link "Benutz"} Usage

                           @{" " link "Sonst"} Author

                           @{" " link "Hist"} History


 Sorry, for my poor english. If you want, you can translate my german guide
 and send to me. You can find the german guide in the Aminet.

                            biz/swood/fw_font.lha

 Thanks.
@ENDNODE

@NODE "Install" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

If you use always an other version of £FontLook.fw¨:

1. Copy £FontLook.fw¨ in your FWMacros-Drawer.



If you dont use £FontLook.fw¨:

1. Copy £FontLook.fw¨ in your FWMacros-Drawer.

2. Start programm £RexxMast¨.

3. Start £Finalwriter¨.

4. Open menu "User - Other - Preferences...". 

         * "Action" - New
         * "Name of menu" - FontLook
         * "Command" - "Type" - ARexx-Script
         * "Command" - "Select" (FontLook.fw)
         * "HotKey" - Alt+F10
         * "Accept"
         * "Save"

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Benutz" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"


            Start the macro with the Shortcut Alt+F10.

            You have to do:

            Select if you want to have a codelist or a layout of
            a font.

            Select the screen output. (speed is 100% faster than normal.
            idea from Frank Waechter)
            
            Select the relevant font..

            You can also select the perforation sign, to collect the
            prints of the fonts.

            Last, but not least, you have to select: Save or the
            print output.


                                   Thats all.
@ENDNODE

